==English==

===Verb===
'''[[wing]] [[it]]'''

#{{idiom}} to [[improvise]]; to make things up or figure things out as one goes; or to perform with little or no  [[preparation]]
#:''I don't know their system, but I think I can '''wing it'''.''
#:''I didn't study for today's test, so I'll have to '''wing it'''.''

